deck: An enemy of El, he would be illuminated by a vision.
description:
The twin brother of Kolat and servant of Utor, Brutas was a huge kryptonian in the dark ages of that world. Angry with the death of his brother he wanted to kill him, but it was dissuaded by his master, who had a more insidious idea. An idea which put the stronger El at their mercy.

However when El was prisioner he was contacted by Rao, an vision than Brutas shared. Terrfied by the vision, Brutas understood the error of his ways. So when El was being tortured and in danger of die under a rain of arrows, Brutas make an heroic sacrifice, puting himself in harm's way and saving the life of EL. An sacrifice which give him, at the end, a meaning to his life.
name: Brutas

deck: Wife of El, ancestor of Superman.
description:
A kryptonian girl who lived in the past Krypton in savages times, Laras Lilith was the dauther of Dar Lilith, the favorite of Lord Utor, the god king of his birthing empire.

However, tradegy struck when her father was killed by a savage of name El, who had given great powers by Rao. He was a danger for all the civilization than Lord Utor represented.

However, under the direction of Utor, Laras Lilit was given the task of seduce and corrupt El, a task she did by marring him and deviating him from his assigned task and discovering his weakness. An information she revealed to Lord Utor, who could capture, torture and mutilate El.

However, Laras also discovered the good nature and honesty of El and feel in love with him. She regret her actions and tried to freed El. In the middle of that task, El saw the god Rao who give him a last mission. El forgave Laras, whom he always loved, even in treason. and urged her to ran away from the city. Using his recovered strengh, El destroyed the city, Lord Utor and himself.

Laras, along with El's mother, Mar, and other survivors of the city and the wildlands, leave the place. The linage of El survived in their son.
name: Laras Lilit

deck: The first ancestor of Superman in the past old Krypton.
description: An orphan boy who lived in the dark ages of Krypton, 500.000 years ago, El was adopted by Naton and Mar, an elder couple who raised the boy as their own. In those savages times, El grew to tranform himself in a gentle, stronger man. However his life changed when a group of riders of Lord Utor came close to his village. When Naton and El fight them, the riders were amazed for El mighty strengh. He alone killed two of the stronger members of the riders, but he also was wound in the fight. The people of the village take him to the temple of Rao, searching for a miracle. The priests of the temple discovered than the wound in his cheast resemble the secret mark of Rao. Wonder themselves if the boy was Rao's chosen one, the priest send the boy with the god, who granted amazing powers, far from those of mortal men. The one destined to bring back the golden age of krypton. El was the first of the linage, and direct ancestor of Superman.
name: El

deck: Mighty One gave powers to everyone who sought him out.
description:
Origin

Alzayah Stone was known as the Mighty One. He gave people powers if they so wished.

Major Story Arcs

Malcolm Dragon, Ant, and Spawn came to stop the Mighty One. He used his molecule manipulation on the cave he was residing in to fight them. Once his mask broke he decided to surrender to Malcolm Dragon, but he was killed by Spawn when he stabbed him in the back.

Powers And Abilities

Molecule Manipulation - He could manipulate molecules in the cave he gave people powers in. That included the cave itself.
